      "content": "The \"evolving with new data\" angle sounds okay, but it's a bit soft. The reporter from the Daily Chronicle is going to be blunt—they're going to say, \"The candidate said X on June 1st and is now saying Y on July 15th. Was the first statement a lie, or are they just indecisive?\" If we use the 'new data' line, can we actually back that up with specific policy changes or economic reports that justify the shift? I don't want us to look like we're just making excuses if they dig deeper.",
